{"article_id":"qcUXKHokwUGB6w5b","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Story highlights","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"The federal government is headed for a potential shutdown","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"Republicans have tied the key spending bill to stopping money for Obamacare","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"Large part of Affordable Care Act is set to go into effect on October 1","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"Over the next few days , the drama of a potential government shutdown will collide with the promise of a new health insurance system","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"known as Obamacare .","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"Here are answers to eight of the most pressing questions about both :","depth":4},{"id":7,"text":"1 . What happens on October 1 with Obamacare and the government shutdown ?","depth":4},{"id":8,"text":"First , the health insurance exchanges","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"established by the Affordable Care Act","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"-- or Obamacare --","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"will be open for business .","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"Millions of uninsured Americans will be able to enroll in health plans","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"before the law kicks in on January 1 , 2014 .","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"Second , the U.S. government might `` shut down ''","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"if lawmakers ca n't agree to pass a funding bill","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"that has attached to it a provision","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"to defund Obamacare .","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"These two events are linked .","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"The reason","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"both houses of Congress may not be able to agree on a funding bill","depth":11},{"id":21,"text":"-- also known as a continuing resolution --","depth":11},{"id":22,"text":"is that some senators and representatives see this as their last chance","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"to stop Obamacare .","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"But that 's really where the link ends .","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":7},{"id":26,"text":"Foes go all out","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"to undermine Obamacare","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"Foes go all out","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"to undermine Obamacare","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"02:03","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":7},{"id":34,"text":"Can lawmakers avoid shutdown ?","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"Can lawmakers avoid shutdown ?","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"02:19","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":6},{"id":40,"text":"GOP plan links Obamacare to shutdown","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"GOP plan links Obamacare to shutdown","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"04:30","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":8},{"id":46,"text":"Sen. Ted Cruz 's war on Obamacare","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"Sen. Ted Cruz 's war on Obamacare","depth":11},{"id":50,"text":"02:54","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"Not really .","depth":5},{"id":52,"text":"Most of the funding for Obamacare comes from new taxes and fees , from cost cuts to other programs like Medicare and other types of funding","depth":7},{"id":53,"text":"that carry on even in the event of a government shutdown .","depth":7},{"id":54,"text":"Congress ' research arm , the Congressional Research service , prepared a memo for Republican Sen. Tom Coburn , R-Oklahoma ,","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"that suggested","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"an effort","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"to use the government shutdown as leverage","depth":11},{"id":58,"text":"to force Democrats to delay implementing the law","depth":11},{"id":59,"text":"would not really work","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"because the law will continue","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"regardless of a shutdown .","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"Plus , the law would still be in effect ,","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"so its many new requirements","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"-- everything from forcing insurance companies to cover anyone","depth":13},{"id":65,"text":"who wants insurance","depth":13},{"id":66,"text":"to forcing everyday Americans to carry health insurance","depth":13},{"id":67,"text":"or pay a fine --","depth":13},{"id":68,"text":"would still be in effect , too .","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"3 . Do I have to sign up for a new health insurance plan on October 1","depth":8},{"id":70,"text":"when open enrollment for Obamacare begins ?","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"Maybe --","depth":7},{"id":72,"text":"Take this quick survey","depth":7},{"id":73,"text":"and we 'll find out :","depth":7},{"id":74,"text":"If the answer is yes","depth":11},{"id":75,"text":"-- and this is by far the No . 1 way","depth":12},{"id":76,"text":"Americans get health insurance --","depth":12},{"id":77,"text":"go on about your business .","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"Obamacare does n't really affect you .","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"At least not yet .","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"A lot of people think","depth":13},{"id":81,"text":"that","depth":14},{"id":82,"text":"because of Obamacare ,","depth":15},{"id":83,"text":"fewer companies will offer health insurance , particularly to low-paid workers and retirees .","depth":15},{"id":84,"text":"There is some evidence of this .","depth":12},{"id":85,"text":"These employers would have to pay a per-worker fine to the government ,","depth":14},{"id":86,"text":"but it might be cheaper for them in the long run to pay this fine to the government","depth":15},{"id":87,"text":"rather than offer insurance .","depth":15},{"id":88,"text":"Other companies might cut hours for some workers ,","depth":15},{"id":89,"text":"making them part-timers","depth":16},{"id":90,"text":"working fewer than 30 hours a week","depth":16},{"id":91,"text":"in order to avoid helping pay their health insurance .","depth":14},{"id":92,"text":"But it will take some years to see","depth":13},{"id":93,"text":"if it really comes to pass .","depth":13},{"id":94,"text":"However ,","depth":12},{"id":95,"text":"if you get health insurance at work ,","depth":13},{"id":96,"text":"you could probably drop that coverage","depth":14},{"id":97,"text":"and buy health insurance on the Obamacare exchanges .","depth":14},{"id":98,"text":"But you might not want to .","depth":12},{"id":99,"text":"You wo n't qualify for any government help","depth":14},{"id":100,"text":"to buy your insurance","depth":14},{"id":101,"text":"and your employer would n't be contributing any of the money","depth":14},{"id":102,"text":"it is now .","depth":14},{"id":103,"text":"If the answer is yes ,","depth":10},{"id":104,"text":"go on about your business .","depth":10},{"id":105,"text":"Obamacare does n't really affect you .","depth":8},{"id":106,"text":"At least not yet .","depth":8},{"id":107,"text":"While Obamacare relies on making Medicare more efficient as a way","depth":9},{"id":108,"text":"to pay for some new services for younger people ,","depth":9},{"id":109,"text":"it is not supposed to change the services","depth":9},{"id":110,"text":"offered by Medicare .","depth":9},{"id":111,"text":"One big test of this promise is Medicare Advantage .","depth":9},{"id":112,"text":"These are privately administered insurance plans","depth":10},{"id":113,"text":"that provide Medicare services to seniors .","depth":10},{"id":114,"text":"They cost the government more per person","depth":12},{"id":115,"text":"to provide Medicare .","depth":12},{"id":116,"text":"So , Obamacare seeks to bring their spending back in line with the rest of Medicare .","depth":11},{"id":117,"text":"This could lead to changes in Medicare Advantage options , like gym memberships and other items","depth":11},{"id":118,"text":"that are offered as enticements .","depth":11},{"id":119,"text":"But the same core Medicare services are supposed to remain in effect .","depth":9},{"id":120,"text":"The same goes for Medicaid .","depth":6},{"id":121,"text":"If you get your insurance from one of the 50 state-run Medicaid programs ,","depth":9},{"id":122,"text":"Obamacare should not affect you .","depth":9},{"id":123,"text":"But you 'll have a lot more company in these programs ,","depth":9},{"id":124,"text":"which will grow","depth":10},{"id":125,"text":"to insure a larger portion of Americans .","depth":10},{"id":126,"text":"If yes ,","depth":8},{"id":127,"text":"Obamacare is going to affect you .","depth":8},{"id":128,"text":"It is possible that your insurance plan wo n't change ,","depth":8},{"id":129,"text":"but it 's just as likely that your plan does n't meet all the minimum requirements","depth":12},{"id":130,"text":"the law imposes .","depth":12},{"id":131,"text":"These include new rules","depth":12},{"id":132,"text":"for how much profit companies can take for plans , new rules for coverage of women 's services , new rules","depth":13},{"id":133,"text":"for how much more insurance companies can charge for women than men , and a lot more .","depth":13},{"id":134,"text":"So , you might have to buy a more expensive plan .","depth":10},{"id":135,"text":"In this case , your insurance company has probably already let you know .","depth":9},{"id":136,"text":"It 's also possible you might want a new plan .","depth":8},{"id":137,"text":"Check out your new state health insurance exchange or the one","depth":10},{"id":138,"text":"the federal government set up in your state","depth":10},{"id":139,"text":"if your state government refused to do so .","depth":9},{"id":140,"text":"People","depth":11},{"id":141,"text":"who like and dislike Obamacare","depth":11},{"id":142,"text":"have something to like about costs of individual plans .","depth":10},{"id":143,"text":"Prelminary estimates have come in lower","depth":12},{"id":144,"text":"than some government prognosticators expected .","depth":12},{"id":145,"text":"So it is fair to say","depth":12},{"id":146,"text":"Obamacare might be cheaper","depth":13},{"id":147,"text":"than expected for some individuals .","depth":13},{"id":148,"text":"But it is also accurate to say","depth":11},{"id":149,"text":"that premiums are likely to rise for healthy people on the individual market .","depth":11},{"id":150,"text":"Why ?","depth":9},{"id":151,"text":"They 're going to get more robust insurance plans","depth":11},{"id":152,"text":"that cover more things .","depth":11},{"id":153,"text":"At the same time , a lot of sick people","depth":13},{"id":154,"text":"who get private insurance","depth":13},{"id":155,"text":"now pay a ton for it ;","depth":12},{"id":156,"text":"their costs could decrease .","depth":11},{"id":157,"text":"If so ,","depth":11},{"id":158,"text":"Obamacare is for you ,","depth":12},{"id":159,"text":"like it or not .","depth":12},{"id":160,"text":"You 're either going to have to enroll in Medicaid","depth":11},{"id":161,"text":"or buy health insurance from a private company on an `` exchange ''","depth":12},{"id":162,"text":"organized by either your state government or the federal government .","depth":12},{"id":163,"text":"If you 're single","depth":13},{"id":164,"text":"and you make less than $ 15,281.70","depth":14},{"id":165,"text":"( $ 31,321.50 for a family of four ) ,","depth":14},{"id":166,"text":"you 're likely to get Medicaid ,","depth":13},{"id":167,"text":"although some states have refused to expand their programs .","depth":13},{"id":168,"text":"Those income levels for Medicaid","depth":14},{"id":169,"text":"-- 133 % of the federal poverty level --","depth":14},{"id":170,"text":"will increase from year to year .","depth":13},{"id":171,"text":"It depends .","depth":12},{"id":172,"text":"What if you make more than $ 15,281.70 , but not that much more ?","depth":15},{"id":173,"text":"You do n't get Medcaid .","depth":15},{"id":174,"text":"You do n't have employer-sponsored health insurance","depth":15},{"id":175,"text":"and you do want coverage .","depth":15},{"id":176,"text":"How are you supposed to afford a new health insurance plan ?","depth":13},{"id":177,"text":"The government is going to help a lot of people pay for it .","depth":13},{"id":178,"text":"If you 're single","depth":17},{"id":179,"text":"and you make less than $ 45,960","depth":18},{"id":180,"text":"( $ 94,200 for a family of four ) ,","depth":18},{"id":181,"text":"you 'll qualify for a government-sponsored subsidy","depth":17},{"id":182,"text":"to help you buy insurance .","depth":17},{"id":183,"text":"The Kaiser Family Foundation has estimated","depth":17},{"id":184,"text":"the average government subsidy for a family will be about $ 2,700","depth":18},{"id":185,"text":"and the average premium costs will be about $ 8,250 .","depth":18},{"id":186,"text":"Those costs will vary","depth":17},{"id":187,"text":"depending on the age and number of family members and the level of plan","depth":18},{"id":188,"text":"they choose to buy .","depth":18},{"id":189,"text":"Try your own scenario here .","depth":15},{"id":190,"text":"No .","depth":16},{"id":191,"text":"Many state Medicaid programs will grow","depth":17},{"id":192,"text":"to insure much larger portions of their state populations .","depth":17},{"id":193,"text":"But the core of the law is the creation of new health insurance exchanges .","depth":12},{"id":194,"text":"These are places","depth":14},{"id":195,"text":"-- online , mostly --","depth":14},{"id":196,"text":"where people","depth":15},{"id":197,"text":"who do n't get insurance","depth":15},{"id":198,"text":"can buy it from a private company .","depth":14},{"id":199,"text":"On the one hand , the government is making people either carry insurance","depth":11},{"id":200,"text":"or pay a fine ,","depth":11},{"id":201,"text":"on the other hand the government is making insurance companies provide insurance to anyone","depth":12},{"id":202,"text":"who wants it","depth":12},{"id":203,"text":"and they 're controlling how much the insurance companies can charge .","depth":11},{"id":204,"text":"You 're young and healthy .","depth":12},{"id":205,"text":"You do n't really want health insurance .","depth":12},{"id":206,"text":"No sweat .","depth":11},{"id":207,"text":"You do n't have to buy it .","depth":12},{"id":208,"text":"You can `` opt out . ''","depth":12},{"id":209,"text":"But then you 'll have to pay a fine of between $ 95 for every adult in your house or 1 % of your income after $ 10,000 , whichever is larger .","depth":12},{"id":210,"text":"So","depth":14},{"id":211,"text":"if you 're single","depth":16},{"id":212,"text":"and you make $ 50,000 ,","depth":16},{"id":213,"text":"you 'd have to pay a $ 400 fine","depth":16},{"id":214,"text":"for not having health insurance .","depth":16},{"id":215,"text":"The Supreme Court called this fine a tax .","depth":14},{"id":216,"text":"You can look at it that way .","depth":15},{"id":217,"text":"Or you can view it as an upfront payment","depth":17},{"id":218,"text":"for having hospital and ambulance services able to come get you","depth":18},{"id":219,"text":"if you need them .","depth":18},{"id":220,"text":"Or you can look at it as horrible government overreach .","depth":17},{"id":221,"text":"Some people do .","depth":17}],"relations":[{"parent":443,"left":0,"right":442,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":442,"left":245,"right":441,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":245,"left":227,"right":244,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":227,"left":226,"right":6,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":226,"left":224,"right":225,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":224,"left":223,"right":3,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":223,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":225,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"p